title: overflow evaluating the requirement `[closure@main.rs:41:17: 41:38]: std::ops::Fn<(&i32,)>
body:
Hi Rust team
I am pretty new to Rust, but believe I might have found a bug in the rustc compiler that causes the trait checker to loop. Here's the program I am trying to compile:
```rust

struct BinTree<V> {
    left: Option<Box<BinTree<V>>>,
    right: Option<Box<BinTree<V>>>,
    value: V
}

impl<V> BinTree<V> {

    fn infix_dfs<F: Fn(&V)>(&self, f: &F) {

        match &self.left {
            Some(left_subtree) => left_subtree.infix_dfs(&f),
            None => {}
        }

        f(&self.value);

        match &self.right {
            Some(right_subtree) => right_subtree.infix_dfs(&f),
            None => {}
        }
    }
}

fn main() {
    let t = BinTree {
        value: 42i32,
        left: Some(Box::new(BinTree {
            value: 37i32,
            left: None,
            right: None
        })),
        right: Some(Box::new(BinTree {
            value: 12i32,
            left: None,
            right: None
        }))
    };

    t.infix_dfs(&|a| println!("{}", a));
}

``` 
The platform I try to compile it on is:
```
stable-x86_64-pc-windows-gnu
rustc 1.37.0 (eae3437df 2019-08-13)
```
And the error message I get is:
